# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js project following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Implemented

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package (version installed: latest)
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the dependency tree

### 2. Component Integration
Modified `/app/layout.tsx` to integrate Speed Insights:
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component within the `<body>` tag, positioned after the `<Footer />` component
- This placement ensures the Speed Insights tracking code is loaded on all pages of the application

## Implementation Details

### Framework-Specific Approach
- Project uses Next.js 16.2.9 (App Router)
- Followed Next.js-specific installation instructions from the Vercel documentation
- Used the `/next` export path for the SpeedInsights component as recommended for Next.js 13.5+

### Files Modified
1. **app/layout.tsx** - Added SpeedInsights component to root layout
2. **package.json** - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
3. **package-lock.json** - Updated with new dependency tree

### Package Manager
- Used npm (detected from existing package-lock.json)
- All dependencies installed successfully

